---
title: Creamy Double-Cheddar Broccoli Risotto with Scallions & Crispy Fried Onions
description: The rich, cozy flavors of broccoli cheddar soup come together with short-grain arborio rice for this hearty weeknight risotto. White cheddar cheese melts into the creamy rice along with tender roasted broccoli. Even more cheddar is sprinkled over the top, and a sprinkle each of scallion greens and crispy fried onions add color and crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66c3865d5cb721784e6369a4-9e7207e9.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66c3865d5cb721784e6369a4-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 890 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 27 g
  carbohydrates: 81 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1230 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-double-cheddar-broccoli-risotto-66c3865d5cb721784e6369a4
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a #medium pot{},
bring 5 cups water to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1}(cut into bite-size pieces if necessary). Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, separating whites from greens).

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While broccoli roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium
heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.
Add @arborio rice{3/4%cup} and stir until evenly coated, ~{15-20%seconds}.

Carefully add 1 cup simmering water to pan with rice mixture. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining
water—adding 1/2 cup at a time and stirring until liquid has absorbed—until rice
is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little less
> water.

Reduce heat to medium low. Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce},
@Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Once risotto is done, remove from heat; stir in broccoli, @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup},
and @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and combined. Taste and season with salt
and pepper if desired.

> Risotto should be a little loose and saucy right before serving; it will
> thicken as it cools. If too thick, stir in water 1 TBSP at a time.

Divide risotto between bowls; top with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}(yellow, shredded),
@crispy fried onions{1}, and scallion greens. Serve.